project.title: Hippopura Sanctuary
project.description:
For my final Thesis Project at university, I decided to create a Real-Time Unreal Engine 4 Environment, applying my knowledge about stylized  PBR Game-Environments on a bigger scale. I had the absolute pleasure to work with Jourdan Tuffan's amazing Hippopura Concept! https://www.artstation.com/artwork/Xnnxwa 
Big thank you to him for agreeing to let me recreate it in 3D for my thesis. 

 I applied a lot of new and old techniques to this piece, which made this a great learning experience. I had roughly 2 months time for working on this, which meant I had to stick to a tight schedule. 
I went for a mix of trim sheets and tiling textures, while also integrating unique modular pieces, which I was able to mix and match with the tiling textures. All assets and shaders seen in the environment are created by me. 
Big thank you to Ryan Pocock https://www.artstation.com/autumnpioneer for supporting me during this time and helping me with the fish blueprints :) And also to Kem Yaralioglu https://www.artstation.com/kem1995 for giving me advice early on!

project.title: LearnSquared - Character Creator
project.description: One of my favourite parts of creating my Learn Squared class 'Designing Better Characters' was creating this 'character creator' in Photoshop.  I love using this technique for clients, as it allows you to create lots of variations on a character and sort of play around with all the different kind of options. Aside from that, it's super fun to do! These are the variations I came up with during the course, but the possibilities are pretty much endless (depending on the work you put in!).

project.title: SUN EATER - fanart
project.description:
This is the fanart for Dylan Sprouse's comic book named "Sun Eater" . Here is the short description of the comic:
"Sun Eater is a twelve-issue saga that takes place in ninth century Norway, where a drug-addled warrior sacrifices his leg to the Gods.  In return he is fused with a parasitic beast, giving him the power to rescue his son from his sworn enemies—history’s first Norwegian king and his five personal guards. The result is a grim and bloody adventure—a dark metaphor for drug addiction, selfishness, and the children it affects."
Pretty awesome stuff, make sure to check it out.

project.title: The Abduction of Nah-ee-lah.
project.description: Sculpture inspired by the novel The Moon Maid, written by Edgar Rice Burroughs. Image portrayer by many artists, including Roy Krenkel, Frank Frazetta or Sanjulian to name some. The creature has been mistakenly portrayed as a Centaur as they are actually Va Gas, an alien race created by E. R. Burroughs but I think centaurs are just more cool. The girl is one of the main characters, called Nah-ee-lah.

project.title: Satanic Vampire Ki-Yeong
project.description:
This is the main character for a Short film i'm making, her name is Ki-Yeong the Angel Slayer, she is a 200 year old Satanic Vampire which is a vampire that has chosen to worship Baphomet instead of Dracula. She operates as a mercenary but swears allegiance to Baphomet. She was given the title of Angel Slayer during the Holy war were she was one of Hell's fiercest and most brutal warriors and became addicted to angel blood and would go out of her way to hunt down angels to feed and enslave. She is into Sadomasochism and is extremely cruel, deviant and promiscuous.

One of the inspirations for this character was mashing together Doomslayer and Bayonetta.
